    <content>&lt;b&gt;Marketing Science&lt;/b&gt; &lt;br&gt;We show that B2B buyers pay more for the same good to sellers with whom they have a social tie (i.e., the individual seller is their ex-employee) and in return get access to higher supply reliability.</content>
